    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Cornelis de Schepper to Miklós Oláh (Dubrovnik, 31 March
                    1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He has finally made it to Dubrovnik. He has learnt that
                            Lodovico Gritti is still in Constantinople and is waiting for Hayreddin
                            Barbarossa Pasha. Ibrahim Pargalı Pasha is said to have fled from the
                            shah, but Schepper is still waiting for more reliable information on
                            everything. Except for three sanjak-beys, all have returned to Asia,
                            which suggests that there will be no peace there now. Myhalibegouitz is
                            said to have sieged the castle of Klis, to avenge Krusics’ sin. Soon
                            they will know more, and he will write in more detail, too.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao suo salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Contranitentibus ventis decem et octo diebus fui in mari Hadriaco.
                    Tandem perveni <placeName>Rhagusium</placeName>, ubi, quod ad
                        <persName>Griti</persName><note xml:id="note.1">Lodovico Gritti.</note>
                    attinet, intellexi illum adhuc esse <placeName>Constantinopoli</placeName>,
                    exspectareque adventum <persName>Barbarossae</persName>,<note xml:id="note.2"
                        >Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha.</note> qui concessit in
                        <placeName>Syriam</placeName> ad <persName>Imbrahimum
                        bassam</persName>.<note xml:id="note.3">Ibrahim Pargalı Pasha.</note> Idne
                    sit verum, an aliter se habeat res, non satis scio. Breviter tamen sum
                    resciturus omnia. Hunc <persName>Imbrahimum</persName> aiunt a
                        <persName>Sophy</persName> profligatum esse. Quomodo tamen aut qualiter non
                    satis scitur, ubi primum venissem <placeName>Rhagusium</placeName>, statim
                    expedivi cursorem ad Sansachum Hertzogonniae et ad <persName>caesarem</persName>
                    Turcarum et ad <persName>Aloisium Gryti</persName>, scripsique ad tres illos in
                    rebus mihi commissis, spero brevi habiturum responsum. Tunc verius et copiosius
                    scribam de omnibus. Nam nunc urget me abitus huius
                        <persName>Hergantini</persName>,<note xml:id="note.4">We do not know him
                        more closely.</note> qui nactus properas ad redeundum tempestates, me cogit
                    esse brevem. Commendo tibi res meas, quae istic sunt; ego vicissim vestrarum
                    rerum curam sum habiturus, de quo mimine convenit dubitare. Omnes Sansachi
                    praeter Samandriae, Bossinae Hertzogoninae, quorum trium vires sunt triginta
                    millia equitum solum, concessere in Asiam: quae res arguit illic non bene
                    succedere negotia. Dicitur et <persName>Myhalibegouytz</persName><note
                        xml:id="note.5">Mihaloğlu Mehmed Bey. In 1517 he was sanjak-bey of Bosnia,
                        in 1520 sanjak-bey of Herzegovina, and he also participated in the battle of
                        Mohács. He then became sanjak-bey of Nikopol, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Babinger</hi> 1993; <hi rend="smallcap">Başar</hi> 2005, 25; <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Sabev</hi> 2013, 232.</note> obsessurus arcem
                        <placeName>Clyssam</placeName><note xml:id="note.6">Klis.</note> ob damna
                    illata a <persName>Petro Crusitz</persName>.<note xml:id="note.7">Péter
                        Krusics.</note> Quid desuper futurum sit, nescio. Fertur etiam magnus caesar
                    Turcarum in persona propria abiturus in Asiam. Brevi sciemus veritatem rei.
                    Commenda servitia mea sacrae reginali maiestati aliisque dominis meis,
                    reverendissimo praesuli <persName>Panormitano</persName>,<note xml:id="note.8"
                        >Jean II Carondelet.</note><persName>duci de Arschot</persName>,<note
                        xml:id="note.9">Philippe II de Croÿ.</note> dominis <persName>de
                        Sanctpy</persName><note xml:id="note.10">Antoine de Croÿ.</note> et
                        <persName>Molenbais</persName> ceterisque, quos una cum Dominatione Tua
                    Christus servet incolumis. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Rhagusii</placeName> ultimo Martii 1534.</p>
            </div>
